eventData.messageText:
The two put a stop to the large hoards of monsters 
and restored herb distribution.

Ready to go back to their own villages, 
the two prepared to leave.

■Young Girl■
"Whew...
That was crazy!"

■Young Boy■
"It was. I really leveled up a bunch..."

■Young Girl■
"Me too, me too! 
I might be the highest level in my village!"

■Young Boy■
"There sure have been a lot of these 
mass monster sightings lately..."

■Young Boy■
"I heard some rumors in town."

■Young Boy■
"This power should come in handy 
if something happens again, but..."

■Young Girl■
"Yeah. 
And I'll work on my herbalism skills!"

■Young Girl■
"My dream is 
to be the best herbalist in the land!"

■Young Boy■
"I could see that! That's great."

■Young Boy■
"You really supported me there.
I'm sure you'll be a great herbalist."

■Young Girl■
"Thanks! I definitely will!"

■Young Girl■
"Leveling up from this fight is 
just the first step towards my dream!"

■Young Girl■
"The town herbalist even remembers me now.
My business might take off!"

■Young Boy■
"You sure have it together."

■Young Boy■
"Honestly, I don't even have a dream..."

■Young Girl■
"Really?"

■Young Girl■
"That a bit surprising!"

■Young Boy■
"Surprising?"

■Young Girl■
"Yeah! You're good at fighting. 
Now that this is done,"

■Young Girl■
"I figured you'd go adventuring 
and solve problems."

■Young Boy■
"Huh... An adventure."

■Young Boy■
"Now that you mention it,
that sort of thing was popular 
a while back."

■Young Girl■
"Yeah! So that's what I figured you'd do."

■Young Girl■
"Large monsters gather underlings
and cause problems for people. 
Like this time."

■Young Girl■
"In fact, 
there were so many adventurers before
that we never saw monsters like this."

■Young Girl■
"That's what the rumors say."

■Young Boy■
"I see..."

■Young Boy■
"If that's true,
then that sounds like a real problem."

■Young Girl■
"Yeah."

■Young Girl■
"Ah, if you do go on an adventure,
be sure to let me join your party!"

■Young Girl■
"They just sound so cool, after all."

■Young Boy■
"There's a lot you want to do."

■Young Boy■
"Anyway... An adventure might be nice."

■Young Boy■
"Ah..."

■Young Girl■
"Oh... This is where we part ways."

■Young Girl■
"Your village is that way, 
and mine is this way..."

■Young Boy■
"Yeah..."

■Young Girl■
"Hehe, 
I'll be sure to visit your village soon!"

■Young Boy■
"Ah, thanks! 
And I'll probably go see you, too."

■Young Girl■
"Alright! I'm looking forward to it."

■Young Girl■
"Thank you so much for today!"

■Young Boy■
"Of course!"

■Young Girl■
"Ehehe, see you later!"

■Young Boy■
"Yeah, later!"
And so, the two returned to their villages.

Their little adventure had ended,
but neither knew that a larger adventure was 
yet to come.
